# Coding Conventions

## Images

**Do NOT use `next/image` (`<Image>`)**. Always use native `<img>` tags.

Reason: `next/image` routes images through `/_next/image?url=...&w=...&q=...` optimization API, generating different URLs per size/quality combination, which invalidates our long-term cache headers set in `next.config.ts` for `/images/*`. For a 390px fixed-width prototype, image optimization is unnecessary.

```tsx
// GOOD
{/* eslint-disable-next-line @next/next/no-img-element */}
<img src="/images/icons/icon-flag.svg" alt="Flag" style={{ width: 24, height: 24 }} />

// BAD
import Image from "next/image";
<Image src="/images/icons/icon-flag.svg" alt="Flag" width={24} height={24} />
```

Always add eslint disable comment when using `<img>`:
```tsx
{/* eslint-disable-next-line @next/next/no-img-element */}
<img src="..." alt="..." />
```

## Icons & Assets

**Strictly export SVG/PNG from Figma designs. Never hand-write or fabricate icons.**

- All icons must be exported from Figma design files via Figma MCP tools, preserving original path data
- **Do NOT** hand-draw SVG paths, cobble together icons, or use placeholders
- Vectors in Figma -> export as SVG
- Rasterized images in Figma -> export as PNG (recommend 3x)
- Save exported files to `public/images/icons/`

## Figma Export vs Code Implementation

**Only export nodes that are image assets (icon / illustration / photo) as SVG/PNG.**
**UI layout, text, lists, grids must be implemented in code. Never screenshot entire blocks as components.**

| Figma Node Type | How to Handle | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Vector / SVG icon | Export SVG | Back arrow, emoji icon, tab bar icon |
| Rasterized image (photo / sticker) | Export PNG (3x) | Avatar, sticker, cover photo |
| Text + layout combo | **Code implementation** | Chat bubble, input bar, nav bar, list |
| Frame with multiple children | **Code implementation**, export child images separately | Sticker grid -> code writes grid, each sticker exported as PNG |

**Forbidden:**
```
- Exporting an entire row of stickers as one PNG -> not interactive
- Exporting tab bar as one image -> can't switch tabs
- Screenshotting chat input bar as component -> can't type text
```

**Correct approach:**
```
- Sticker grid: code implements grid layout, each sticker individually exported from Figma as PNG
- Tab bar: code implements button layout, each icon exported from Figma as SVG
- Input bar: code implements flex layout + <input>, camera/emoji icons exported as SVG
```

## Animations

All animations use **[motion](https://motion.dev)** (package: `motion`, import from `"motion/react"`).

### Import convention

```tsx
import { motion, AnimatePresence } from "motion/react";
```

- Use `<motion.div>` / `<motion.button>` etc. for animated elements.
- Wrap conditionally rendered animated elements with `<AnimatePresence>` for exit animations.
- Always add a stable `key` prop when the animated element can swap (e.g. reaction emoji changing).

### Spring presets

Use spring physics for all interactive / UI animations. **Do NOT use** ease / cubic-bezier easing.

```ts
// Fast & snappy - buttons, pills, pop-in elements
const springPop = { type: "spring", stiffness: 700, damping: 35 };

// Slightly softer - panels, cards, context menus
const springGentle = { type: "spring", stiffness: 600, damping: 32 };
```

### Timing guidelines

| Category | Duration / Delay | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Backdrop fade (overlay) | `duration: 0.15` | Short tween, no spring |
| Panel enter/exit | Use `springPop` | scale + y offset |
| Staggered children | `delay: 0.02 * index` | 20ms between each child |
| Secondary panel delay | `delay: 0.02` | Slight delay for context menu etc |
| Reaction pill pop | `springPop` (stiffness 700, damping 30) | scale from 0.3, transformOrigin at bubble corner |

### Common patterns

```tsx
// Overlay backdrop (tween, not spring)
<motion.div
  initial={{ backgroundColor: "rgba(0,0,0,0)" }}
  animate={{ backgroundColor: "rgba(0,0,0,0.45)", backdropFilter: "blur(6px)" }}
  exit={{ backgroundColor: "rgba(0,0,0,0)" }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.15 }}
/>

// Panel scale-in
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, scale: 0.85, y: -12 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, scale: 1, y: 0 }}
  exit={{ opacity: 0, scale: 0.85, y: -12 }}
  transition={springPop}
/>

// Pill pop-in with AnimatePresence
<AnimatePresence>
  {value && (
    <motion.div
      key={value}
      initial={{ opacity: 0, scale: 0.3 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, scale: 1 }}
      exit={{ opacity: 0, scale: 0.3 }}
      transition={{ type: "spring", stiffness: 700, damping: 30 }}
    />
  )}
</AnimatePresence>

// Tap feedback
<motion.button whileTap={{ scale: 1.35 }} />
```
